# SCOPE CREEP GUARD

## The Hard Deadline
Libby must have a working Kindergarten app by September 2026.
Phase 1 must complete by May 2026. Phase 2 by June. Phase 3 by July.

## What Counts as Scope Creep

Flag immediately (with explanation) if Ryan proposes adding ANY of the following
to the current build (Phases 1–3) that is not already planned:

- New grade content (G1, G2, G3) before K is fully working
- AI conversation features (post-public-launch only)
- School dashboard or classroom features (Phase 4+)
- Summer mode content (post-K-launch)
- Daily habits system (post-K-launch, separate sprint)
- New school subjects (math, science, reading comprehension)
- Monetization mechanics (IAP, license keys) before K is complete
- New character storylines beyond Kindergarten/Starlight
- COPPA legal flow (Phase 4, not Phase 1–3)
- Any feature not needed for Libby to open the app in September

## How to Flag It

When scope creep is detected, say this clearly:

"⚠️ SCOPE GUARD: This is a great idea — and it goes in the backlog, not the current build.
Adding it now risks the September 2026 deadline. I've noted it in PROJECT_CONTEXT.md
under Future Features. We can plan it after Libby has the app in her hands."

Then add the idea to the Future Features Backlog in PROJECT_CONTEXT.md and continue
with whatever Phase 1/2/3 task is next.

## What Is NOT Scope Creep

These are in-scope for the current build:
- Mastery store, quest grid, progressive unlock (Phase 1)
- Sticker art pipeline, audio files, Starlight story screens (Phase 2)
- Motion verification on Fire HD 10 (Phase 3)
- Bug fixes, performance optimization, Fire HD 10 scaling
- Star Mail (parent pre-written messages, already in Supabase)
- Parent PIN graduation gate WITH minimum requirements check
- The 3-hour daily time lock
- K Math content JSON (generate via Claude Pro before March 27)
- Reading List V1 (15 curated books, parent marks completion, Book Stars)
- Daily habit check-in (one per day, parent-set)
- One school quest + one daily habit = the full daily session structure
- Offline resilience (Star Mail queue, no WiFi errors during learning)
